JAX-RS API
Jersey REST framework

1) https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/jersey.github.io/documentation/latest/getting-started.html
2) read getting started
3) figure out maven dependencies
4) add maven dependies to jpaclassic project
5) implement & test "getting started" rest demo
6) create rest ressource for any shop entity
7) serve & test entity pk via GET operation
8) add maven dependency of json parser/generator to project (eg https://github.com/google/gson)
9) replace entity pk in get operation with shop entity serialized in json
10) implement other operations/resources
11) profit 


Jersey Dependencies

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.glassfish.jersey.containers</groupId>
    <artifactId>jersey-container-grizzly2-http</artifactId>
    <version>2.29.1</version>
</dependency>

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.glassfish.jersey.inject</groupId>
    <artifactId>jersey-hk2</artifactId>
    <version>2.29.1</version>
</dependency>

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.glassfish.jersey.media</groupId>
    <artifactId>jersey-media-json-binding</artifactId>
    <version>2.29.1</version>
</dependency>
